R", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Running a `ui` test will eventually invoke the following function:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/4ca19e09d302a4cbde14f9cb1bc109179dc824cd/src/tools/compiletest/src/read2.rs#L48-L57\r\n\r\nthrough\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/4ca19e09d302a4cbde14f9cb1bc109179dc824cd/src/tools/compiletest/src/runtest.rs#L1772-L1780\r\n\r\nwhich can truncate a long output from the compiler. The problem is that UI tests ask the compiler to output its output as json and then attempts to parse it later, for example here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/4ca19e09d302a4cbde14f9cb1bc109179dc824cd/src/tools/compiletest/src/runtest.rs#L3114\r\n\r\nwhich can fail due to truncation and output very difficult to investigate output in e.g. CI.\r\n\r\nReference: https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187780-t-compiler.2Fwg-llvm/topic/Legacy.20PM.20removal/near/279479951", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96229/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96229/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}